            <title>[DERBY-1024] Client&apos;s XAResource.start throws XAException with XAER_RMFAIL when local transaction is active</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-1024</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;perform some work in a local transaction without committing and then start a global transaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Embedded throws an XAException with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;XAER_OUTSIDE - The resource manager is doing work outside a global transaction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Client throws an XAEception with&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;XAER_RMFAIL  -  Resource manager is unavailable&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems like embedded has the correct error code, though I don&apos;t have the XA spec in front of me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
